spanGrp.span: welwel gil aa gab quut qamuunyaand
I'm of the clan of Qahooga
geebiit mitaala amuuch qwahiid aa gebalaagji
We stayed a lot in Matala until later we moved
When we arrived in Mang'ola, well we lived
qay buneed gwand gabigd gabuugd ng'wakaal
In the old days there were people returning to Ng'wakala
And later we came to Mang'ola
ng'asheeg gik aa midamuus daraad ab gidab aseas geawaasch manaang'i
Those things I won't be able to say, because we were small
mambo yale mimi sitayaweza kuyakuta kwa sababu sisi tulikuwa wadogo
For the stories they were saying
haya qay asimjeeg iihindaytiin aa qwadaard ab ea
Okay, well the Asimjeeg, after scattering there
haya basi waasimjega baada ya kutawanyiika huko
When they scattered to go to Ng'wakal
Others passed, they went to Law
aseas aa iidu aa mebuugdaan ng'wakaal aseas geedoobiw aa ewayeen mang'ool
Well, we didn't return to Ng'wakal, we headed to the east until we reached Mang'ola
basi sisi hatukurudi ng´wakala tukaelekea mashariki hadi kufika mang´ola
And in the old days the leader of the land was Ginanana
na zamani mtemi wa nchi alikuwa ginanana
aa muuch qwahiid ha aa edariida
qawuuny aa doan ng'anyiin ba lawuun
I came until I arrived in this area of Law
nikaja hadi nikafika hiyo sehemu ya musoma
After arriving in this area of Law
baada ya juwa nimeshafika kwenye nchi hii ya musoma
as aniin stoariijeeg qay ba qay ba jiriing'd aniin midanaal
So me, those storied of the beginning, I won't be able to know them
kwa hiyo mimi zile historia za mwanzo mimi sitaweza kujua
Well, this is how it was
The way I know is this
gwand gil nuut ja eeng'eat qana
Is there something else to start, or?
kuna kitu kingine cha kuanza au
